.TH POLKITGUARD 1 "April 2026" "PolkitGuard 1.5.0"
.SH NAME
polkitguard \- Security scanner for Linux Polkit configurations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B polkitguard
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
PolkitGuard scans Linux Polkit configuration files for security issues and vulnerabilities.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR \fI/path\fR
Custom path to scan (default: system polkit directories)
.TP
\fB\-\-severity\fR \fIlevel\fR
Minimum severity level to report (low, medium, high, critical)
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fIfmt\fR
Output format: text, json, html, sarif, csv
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR \fIfile\fR
Path to config file (JSON), use '-' for stdin
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fIfile\fR
Output file path
.TP
\fB\-\-summary\fR
Show summary only (counts)
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Show version
.TP
\fB\-\-no-color\fR
Disable colored output
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB\-q\fR
Quiet mode (suppress banner)
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message
.SH CONFIG FILE
Config file locations (in order):
.IP \(bu 2
./polkitguard.json
.IP \(bu 2
config.json
.IP \(bu 2
~/.config/polkitguard.json
.IP \(bu 2
/etc/polkitguard.json
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
0
No security issues found
.TP
1
Low severity issues found
.TP
2
Medium severity issues found
.TP
3
High severity issues found
.TP
4
Critical issues found
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan default locations:
.B polkitguard
.TP
High severity only:
.B polkitguard \-\-severity high
.TP
JSON output:
.B polkitguard \-\-format json
.TP
Scan custom path:
.B polkitguard \-\-path /etc/polkit\-1/localauthority
.SH SEE ALSO
polkitd(8), pkaction(1), pkexec(1)
